hips, world-class labour, and progressive governance in a digital sphere. Ultimately, YouTube and Brokerage Dynamics in Philippine Digital Cultures offers a fresh, compelling, and nuanced account of YouTube as an important site for the mediation of culture, economy, and politics in Philippine postcolonial modernity amid rapid economic globalisation and digitalisation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aInternet videosxPolitical aspectszPhilippines. 0aInternet videosxSocial aspectszPhilippines. 0aOnline social networksxPolitical aspectszPhilippines. 0aOnline social networksxSocial aspectszPhilippines. 4aAsian Studies. 4aContemporary Society. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDigital and Social Media. 4aInternet and digital media: arts and performance. 4aMedia Studies. 4aMedia studies: internet, digital media and society. 4aSociety and culture: general. 4aSouth East Asia. 7aCOMPUTERS / Digital Media / General.2bisacsh  aYouTube, digital media, social transactions, brokering, postcolonialism, mestiso, mestisa, humour, interracial relationships, freelance work, democracy, populism, Philippine politics, agency, and paradox.1 aCabalquinto, Earvin Charles, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048552443?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048552443423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048552443/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076709-4  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCO